chap. 45</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note39" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref39
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">39</A>
Between Raetia and Pannonia, the northern frontier being the Danube from Passau nearly to Vienna.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note40" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref40
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">40</A>
A friendly branch of the Suebi, north of Raetia, to which they were allowed free access: see
	<A HREF="
https://elfinspell.com/TacitusGermany4.html#refch41
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Germ.</I> 41</A>. Vibilius appears again in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/12A*.html#29
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="small">XII</SPAN>.29</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note41" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref41
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">41</A>
On the Via Aurelia, which ran to Arles. Now Fréjus, in the <I>département</I> of Var.<A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(CarelessLoeb70+'Vat</SPAN>',WIDTH,216)"
onMouseOut="nd();">º</A>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note42" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref42
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">42</A>
In Moravia and Upper Hungary; neighbours of the Marcomani, with whom they played a leading part in the great barbarian coalition against Rome under Marcus Aurelius. — For the fate of Vannius' kingdom see
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/12A*.html#29
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="small">XII</SPAN>.29‑30</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note43" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref43
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">43</A>
Marus is the March (Morava); Cusus, the Waag or Gran or Gusen.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note44" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref44
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">44</A>
Built in the Forum of Augustus to commemorate his vengeance on the slayers of the dictator Julius. For its military associations, <I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Augustus*.html#29
	"TARGET="Suetonius_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EPlusL,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Suet. <I>Aug.</I> 29</A>;
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/ovid/ovid.fasti5.shtml
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Book 5<BR>of Ovid\'s Fasti'+Lat2+LatSearch+'praetextum</SPAN>',WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Ov. <I>Fast.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">V</SPAN>.567 <I>sqq.</I></A>; and below
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/3A*.html#18
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="small">III</SPAN>.18
	</A>
and
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/13A*.html#8
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="small">XIII</SPAN>.8</A>. A few columns still remain.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note45" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref45
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">45</A>
The country only became a province under Claudius (46 <SPAN CLASS="small">A.D.</SPAN>). Under Tiberius, with the exception of the southern coast on the Aegean (which belonged to the province of Macedonia) and the Thracian Chersonese (which was private imperial property), it was governed by <SPAN CLASS="whole">semi-independent</SPAN> native princes.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note46" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref46
