E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2C*.html#ref59
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">59</A>
The northern colossus of the two at <SPAN CLASS="whole">Medînet-Habu</SPAN>, which represent Ȧmen-ḥetep III (<I>ca.</I> 1450 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>). Another imperial antiquary, in the person of Hadrian, has left his name on the statue: the "vocal sound" of the familiar story ceased when the colossus was restored by Severus.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
